      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/39/741",
      "text": [
        " اَلْبِسَاطِ لَهَا عَيْنَانِ وَ أَنْتَ تُصَلِّي فَقَالَ «إِنْ كَانَ لَهَا عَيْنٌ وَاحِدَةٌ فَلاَ بَأْسَ وَ إِنْ كَانَ لَهَا عَيْنَانِ وَ أَنْتَ تُصَلِّي فَلاَ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.741 – He, Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as), was asked about images on a carpet that have two eyes while you are praying.\nImam (as) said: \"If it has one eye, then there is no harm, but if it has two eyes and you are praying, then it is not permissible.\""
        ]
      }
    },
